Previously (message 1393) I posted about problems I
was having invoking the AList methods that were
moved back into CandidateURI from CrawlURI in
heritrix-1.3.0.  I have done further tests with 
these puzzling results:

(1) The problem posted earlier
org.archive.crawler.datamodel.CrawlURI.ContainsKey(String)
method not found.
(But the compiler had no problem with curi.ContainsKey(x)).

(2) Does a cast make a difference? no.  Code:

     // Run a quick test on the new AList arrangement
     ((CandidateURI)bundle).putString("JunkKey", "junk");

Runtime error:
org.archive.crawler.datamodel.CandidateURI.putString(String,String)
not found.  Neither CrawlURI.AListmethod nor CandidateURI.AListmethod
can be found.  It's not an inheritance problem.

(3) How about methods other than the recently moved AList methods? 
Experiment with isSeed():  The code (bundle is a CrawlURI):

System.out.println(ME+"CrawlURI.isSeed() is " + bundle.isSeed());
System.out.println(ME+"CandidateURI.isSeed() is " +     
((CandidateURI)bundle).isSeed());

Result: runs fine.  No run-time errors.  Correct answers printed out.

Why can the compiler compile my code OK (finds the AList methods)
but the runtime can't?  Why are the older CandidateURI methods all
OK at run-time, but the newly added AList methods not?  

Puzzled, D.
